cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS

The paper deals with optimization problems related to low-rank matrices, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses matrix completion and robust PCA, which are subfields of computer vision and signal processing, respectively, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IT (Information Theory) likely categories as well. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category. Finally, the paper presents a new framework that simplifies existing analyses, which could make it relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category.
